rather than hairless tails. Dormice have an
excellent sense of hearing. They eat
flowers during the spring, fruit in summer
and nuts in fall. Dormice are well known
for their habit of sleeping for as much as
seven months of the year. At the onset of
colder weather in October, the animals build
a nest and go to sleep until April. They
produce between two and seven young at a
time. The young dormice stay with their
mother until they are about ten weeks old.
